  "text": "The gRPC health check protocol compliance implementation in Envoy v1.31.2 is primarily located in the health checkers extension module. The main C++ source files are in source/extensions/health_checkers/grpc/.\n\n## Core Implementation\n\n**GrpcHealthCheckerFactory** (source/extensions/health_checkers/grpc/health_checker_impl.h/cc): Factory class registered as 'envoy.health_checkers.grpc' that creates health checker instances. The createCustomHealthChecker() method instantiates ProdGrpcHealthCheckerImpl with appropriate cluster and dispatcher context.\n\n**GrpcHealthCheckerImpl** (source/extensions/health_checkers/grpc/health_checker_impl.h/cc): Main health checker implementation that extends HealthCheckerImplBase. In its constructor, it:\n- Looks up the grpc.health.v1.Health.Check service method using Protobuf::DescriptorPool::generated_pool()->FindMethodByName(\"grpc.health.v1.Health.Check\")\n- Parses initial metadata and optional service name and authority values from config\n- Sets up header parsing for initial metadata customization\n\n**GrpcActiveHealthCheckSession** (source/extensions/health_checkers/grpc/health_checker_impl.h/cc): Nested private class within GrpcHealthCheckerImpl that implements the actual health check session protocol. Key responsibilities:\n\n1. **HealthCheckRequest Handling** (onInterval method, line 186-239):\n   - Creates HTTP/2 connection via parent.createCodecClient()\n   - Builds gRPC request headers using Grpc::Common::prepareHeaders() with service method name\n   - Creates grpc::health::v1::HealthCheckRequest protobuf message\n   - Optionally sets the service name field in the request if configured\n   - Serializes request using Grpc::Common::serializeToGrpcFrame()\n   - Encodes request data with proper gRPC framing\n\n2. **Response Headers Processing** (decodeHeaders method, line 96-128):\n   - Validates HTTP/2 200 OK response status\n   - Implements HTTP to gRPC status mapping per https://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/master/doc/http-grpc-status-mapping.md\n   - Checks for grpc-status header in response headers and trailers\n   - Detects invalid gRPC responses and protocol violations\n   - Handles end-of-stream scenarios appropriately\n\n3. **Response Data Processing** (decodeData method, line 130-162):\n   - Decodes gRPC message frames using Grpc::Decoder\n   - Parses grpc::health::v1::HealthCheckResponse from protobuf binary format\n   - Validates frame format and prevents unexpected streaming (unary RPC should have one message)\n   - Handles gRPC wire protocol decode errors\n\n4. **Response Trailers Processing** (decodeTrailers method, line 164-174):\n   - Extracts gRPC status and message from HTTP trailers\n   - Defaults to Internal status if trailers are malformed\n   - Signals completion of RPC\n\n5. **Health Check Status Mapping** (isHealthCheckSucceeded method, line 300-312):\n   - Returns true only when:\n     * gRPC status is Ok (0)\n     * AND health_check_response exists\n     * AND response status equals grpc::health::v1::HealthCheckResponse::SERVING\n   - All other states result in health check failure\n\n6. **Logging with Status Enumeration** (logHealthCheckStatus method, line 365-398):\n   - Maps HealthCheckResponse status values to string representations:\n     * grpc::health::v1::HealthCheckResponse::SERVING → \"serving\"\n     * grpc::health::v1::HealthCheckResponse::NOT_SERVING → \"not_serving\"\n     * grpc::health::v1::HealthCheckResponse::UNKNOWN → \"unknown\"\n     * grpc::health::v1::HealthCheckResponse::SERVICE_UNKNOWN → \"service_unknown\"\n     * Missing response → \"rpc_error\"\n   - Logs combined gRPC status code and message for debugging\n\n## Protocol Compliance Details\n\nThe implementation fully adheres to the grpc.health.v1.Health service specification:\n- Uses standard grpc.health.v1.HealthCheckRequest message format (optional service field)\n- Expects grpc.health.v1.HealthCheckResponse with ServingStatus enum values\n- Implements proper HTTP/2 and gRPC frame handling via Grpc::Common utilities\n- Respects HTTP-to-gRPC status mapping standards\n- Validates unary RPC semantics (single request, single response)\n- Properly extracts gRPC status from headers (when available) or trailers (default)\n\n## Production Implementation\n\n**ProdGrpcHealthCheckerImpl** (source/extensions/health_checkers/grpc/health_checker_impl.h/cc): Production subclass that creates real Http::CodecClientProd instances for actual HTTP/2 connections, enabling actual gRPC health checks against upstream services.\n\n## Base Classes and Integration\n\nThe implementation integrates with the broader health checker framework:\n- Extends HealthCheckerImplBase from source/extensions/health_checkers/common/health_checker_base_impl.h\n- Registered via REGISTER_FACTORY macro for dynamic factory lookup\n- Uses HealthCheckerFactoryContextImpl from source/common/upstream/health_checker_impl.h for dependency injection\n- Follows the health checker plugin architecture allowing multiple checker types (HTTP, TCP, gRPC, custom)"
